	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f102790901099586>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>The Top 2</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jul 28th 10:29 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=178090><span id= >Neodestroyer</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Awful [1.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>From what ive seen and read about is there are two top races for the warrior class.&nbsp;&nbsp;First class is the Barbarian.  After using their the start up points correctly they can start with 130str and 105sta.  In my opinion strength is all power.  Therefore i believe barbarian warriors are more effective with 2hs weapons with this amount of strength.  I know speed is what everyone wants in raids even with a two handed weapon you can get the proper speed to survive.  Barbarians are designed to deal out all the damage in one blow(two or three with double or triple strike).  To some up its your call to make a barbarian warrior dual wield but at the current moment i have a lvl 20 barbarian warrior using a runed frost blade w/ fbss and yes im kinda slow but im in the process of getting shoulderpads that adds haste II. Word of advice my fried is a shd and is 1hs and he deals damage very fast where my damage is stronger but yet slower.<br><br>The second race is the Ogre.  Ogres have very high starting stamina but pretty high strength.  I think this makes them the perfect candidate for dual wielding.  Since they have high stamina they can take alot of hits but at the same time delivering fast damage.  It sounds like ogres are perfect for two hand weapons but ogres with their good but not great strength makes them lean more into dual wielding.<br><br>Im not saying these are the only to races that are good warriors but personally think they are the best.  I have made an iksar warrior and was quite impressed with him.  Anyways whether or not you use this info i just wanted to state my theory.  If your on the prexus server send a tell to Neodestroyer just to say hi or maybe group.  Farewell and happy hunting to all and may you find the right character you will enjoy playing.<br><br>Later<br>Neodestroyer Reaperofpain</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
